An Act requiring a waiting period for new taxes.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 58 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby
2 amended by adding the following new section:-
3 "Section 52. No new tax shall be collected, assessed or payable until 3 months after the
4 passage of the act in which the new tax was created."
